<div id="review_2813462216" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2813462216" />
    <a title="Daniel Clouser" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/49093956-daniel-clouser"><img alt="Daniel Clouser" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1447798419p2/49093956.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2813462216?book_show_action=true">May 20, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Daniel Clouser" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Daniel Clouser" href="/user/show/49093956-daniel-clouser">Daniel Clouser</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2813462216" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8099249561731269850">Ah, Night Angel. What to say about the trilogy? So popular, but such a mess. I&apos;m glad it gave the world Brent Weeks, as Lightbringer is among my favorite series, but Night Angel has problems.<br/><br/>It&apos;s not that there isn&apos;t a good story there, but the execution is uneven. Major revelations often don&apos;t hit right: rather than everything clicking into place, twists come out of left field. Chapters will skip around between POVs, seemingly at random, sometimes.<br/><br/>Some elements seem derivative of The Wheel of T</span>
  <span id="freeText8099249561731269850" style="display:none">Ah, Night Angel. What to say about the trilogy? So popular, but such a mess. I'm glad it gave the world Brent Weeks, as Lightbringer is among my favorite series, but Night Angel has problems.<br /><br />It's not that there isn't a good story there, but the execution is uneven. Major revelations often don't hit right: rather than everything clicking into place, twists come out of left field. Chapters will skip around between POVs, seemingly at random, sometimes.<br /><br />Some elements seem derivative of The Wheel of Time (the Lae'knaught are exactly like the White Cloaks, and the Chantry is rrrreeeeaaaaallly close to the Aes Sedai, for example). If they'd been developed more, maybe they would have seemed more like a tribute than a ripoff.<br /><br />The third book goes all out with high fantasy standards like prophecies and godlike forces, but like the Wheel of Time-esque elements, this sudden escalation of the stakes isn't given proper development. <br /><br />I still gave the series three stars, but I think that the same story could have been told differently and been a five-star effort.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="8099249561731269850" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


